You’ve probably heard of (and dreaded) Mercury retrograde. It’s an astrological event that happens several times a year that causes all sorts of freakouts. Mercury Retrograde has just ended (hooray), but we’re not totally in the clear. All planets have their own retrogrades, and while we’re out of Mercury’s, we’re about to head into Saturn’s. A retrograde is when a planet appears to be spinning backward, from our vantage point on Earth. It’s actually an optical illusion. The Earth is completing its orbit around the Sun faster than other planets outside its orbit. Periodically, it will outpace them — and that’s when they are said to go retrograde. And, at its most basic level, it means their influence goes from a positive to a negative. The good news: each retrograde brings its own energy, so they’re not all as chaotic as Mercury’s. Saturn’s retrograde starts June 4 and lasts until October 23, in the sign of Aquarius. That’s quite a chunk of time. As a slower-moving outer planet, Saturn creates longer trends. The ringed planet stays in a single zodiac sign for two to three years and takes 29.5 years to orbit the whole Zodiac. Overall, this retrograde will see you questioning your plans and ambition in terms of work, finances, home, family, and responsibility. Are you really creating true and firm foundations for the future? Are you taking ownership for yourself and supporting others? Are you acting maturely and well? Are you a source of reliability and honesty, or are you still acting out and slipping your responsibilities? Saturn is a task master. It is the planet that makes us grow up, shape up, and turn up and do our bit. What might you go back to the drawing board on during this retrograde? Let the tarot guide you, with a Saturn retrograde tarot horoscope for all the star signs. March 21 to April 20 Tarot card for Aries for Saturn retrograde: Two of Cups Meaning: Romantic relationships are a theme for consideration during this retrograde, as well as close friendships and family ties. What role do you play in these circles and partnerships? Are you supportive and positive? Are you something else? Do you like who you are with other people? Reflect on your journey, the ups and downs, the life lessons, the highs and lows. You are adorable and loved, but you can be impetuous, demanding and competitive. Do these behaviours trip you up? Fix relationship dynamics that aren’t working. Head here for everything you need to know about being an Aries April 21 to May 21 Tarot card for Taurus for Saturn retrograde: Queen of Cups Meaning: Your emotional stability and wellbeing is a theme for consideration this retrograde. Are you taking good care of your mental heath? Are you prioritizing deep rest and rejuvenation when you need to? Are you keeping a healthy work/life balance? Are you getting what you need from the people closest to you? Others are not mind readers. They need to know what you need, and that responsibility for expression is on you. Open up and be more overt about your needs. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Taurus May 22 to June 21 Tarot card for Gemini for Saturn retrograde: Page of Coins Meaning: Education and study are your lifeblood. All Geminis love to learn and make it a lifelong hobby. The Page of Coins asks you to consider what role education could play in a more career or financially related sphere this year. Do you need to retrain? Do you lack an important skill necessary to get to the next level? Do you have blind spots in certain, important life areas? Consider and get to making a plan of how you can learn what you now need to know. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Gemini June 22 to July 23 Tarot card for Cancer for Saturn retrograde: Knight of Coins Meaning: Taking responsibility for your work, home, health, and money. This is what ruminates around your mind this retrograde, and you’re feeling a bit defensive. Maybe you know, deep down, you could do more/better, but circumstances have gotten in the way, and you feel the need to defend your actions. Maybe you know you need a stronger security net beneath you and you’re keen to build that. Maybe you feel others have too much say / power over certain aspects on your life and you crave independence. Whatever the issue, now is the time to clarify it, address it, and overcome it. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Cancer July 24 to August 23 Tarot card for Leo for Saturn retrograde: Six of Wands Meaning: You are ready to go further, expand your world, broaden your horizons and build on your existing success and talent. You’ve done really well recently, as shown by the applauding Six of Wands. Well done! Now it’s time to consolidate, build and make this success a long-term thing vs a flash in the pan. Take what’s going well, and do more of it, at a higher level, for greater risks and rewards. Be bold. You are being blessed with good fortune, as long as you try your best to carry on this winning streak. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Leo August 24 to September 23 Tarot card for Virgo for Saturn retrograde: Queen of Wands Meaning: Caution is a virtue of yours but, like all virtues, it has a double edge. The Queen of Wands provokes a realization that sometimes you play too safe, when in doubt you retreat, under pressure you stop. Sometimes you need to push out of your comfort zone, as that’s where the best prizes are. Sometimes you need to take a (mitigated) risk. Sometimes you just have to make a bold leap and have faith in your ability to land well. You are an organised and competent person, and there’s little you can’t handle. Have more faith. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Virgo September 24 to October 23 Tarot card for Libra for this week: Judgment Meaning: You are going through a major life shift this June to October, as shown by the powerful Judgment card. And it’s all about being more authentically you, doing