ring this retrograde. Let them be the first agents of transformation in your world – welcome their presence, thank them for their message, and then move on to creating solutions and fixes. The Five of Swords shows you will experience pressure and conflict in the places that you’re outgrowing, that need renewal, that need a new plan. So don’t obsess or worry about it, instead acknowledge the pressure, understand what isn’t working, and focus on creating inspiring ways forward. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Capricorn January 22 to February 19 Tarot card for Aquarius for Saturn retrograde: Three of Coins Meaning: You can be a bit of a loner, preferring solo projects and personal responsibility. That’s a strength of yours, and serves you well, but you can’t do everything alone. Some things need a team approach, groupwork and collaboration. The Three of Coins asks you to soften your stance about working and co-operating with others to achieve bigger goals. It is for your own benefit, as you can go further, faster. Come out of your shell. Look at bigger ambitions and adopt a team system to reach them. Join in. Contribute. Head here for everything you need to know about being an Aquarius February 20 to March 20 Tarot card for Pisces for Saturn retrograde: King of Cups Meaning: Your friendships, fellowships, and romantic relationships are under the lens this retrograde, and you’re assessing where you find most reward, support, fun and goodwill. The Knight of Cups asks you to trust your gut instincts about the people in your life, and adjust the time and energy you expend with them accordingly. It doesn’t mean cutting people off (well, unless you think that’s a good idea, and it might be), but just being more mindful about being around people who are good for you, and good to you. Head here for everything you need to know about being a Pisces Your daily Metro.co.uk horoscope is here every morning, seven days a week (yes, including weekends!). To che